We cannot thank our Food Services Department enough for their dedication to our students and the Franklin community!

June 8 at 2:35 PM ·

post_text:
May 26, 2020

Dear Franklin Families,

We are writing to share important information with you related to the development of the School Department's FY 21 budget. Attached, you will find a memo to the School Committee outlining anticipated budget shortfalls under two possible scenarios: the Governor's Budget from January and a possible reduction to state aid.

The link to the virtual meeting has been posted as part of the School Committee's agenda as a place for those who wish to participate. The meeting does have a space limit. An alternative way to view the School Committee meeting this evening to learn more about the status of the FY 21 budget is to watch the program live on Comcast Channel 11, Verizon Channel 29, or through Franklin TV livestream: https://www.franklinma.gov/home/pages/live-meetings-stream

Sincerely,

Franklin Public Schools

post_text:
April 14th, 2020

Dear Franklin Families,

Earlier this evening, the Franklin School Committee voted to eliminate four school days of April vacation and hold four days of remote learning. This will provide for continuity at this time. An overwhelming majority of faculty (93%) and families (89.3%) preferred to eliminate vacation, most favoring eliminating four days over three.

Please note that Monday, April 20 is Patriots’ Day, a state holiday and will not be used for remote learning.

This will adjust the end of the school year. According to the most recent guidance from DESE, this would have Franklin Public Schools ending its school year on Thursday, June 18, or our 181st day of school. (We have one snow day to make up from December 2019).

If you have any questions, please contact the Superintendent’s Office at 508-553-4819 and leave a message. Your message will be received via email and returned shortly.

Sincerely,

Franklin Public Schools

post_text:
March 25, 2020

Dear Franklin Families and Faculty/Staff,

As you may know, Governor Baker announced earlier today that he signed an executive order that all Massachusetts schools will remain closed through April, opening no earlier than Monday, May 4, 2020.

Both the Governor and Massachusetts Department of Elementary and Secondary Education (DESE) Commissioner explained how the Department has been working to develop new guidance about Remote Learning in light of this extension. Superintendents are expecting to receive this guidance tomorrow and, after reviewing it, we will follow these guidelines and work cooperatively with the Franklin Education Association to build upon our initial engagement and enrichment since last week.

Per Commissioner Riley’s announcement this afternoon, our plan will begin in early April.

We will continue to keep the community informed as we continue to navigate these unprecedented circumstances. We sincerely hope that you are feeling well and that your families are staying safe.

Kind regards,

Sara Ahern

Superintendent of Schools

post_text:
GREAT NEWS ALERT!!!! FPS is very proud and excited to share an incredible student accomplishment. FHS Senior Drew Conrad won the National Gold Medal Award for his ceramics portfolio from the Scholastic Art & Writing Awards Program.

Drew is 1 of 8 students from around the country in the field of studio art who have been selected for this award! Drew will directly receive a $10,000 scholarship, will participate in a national traveling art exhibition for the next two years, and both Drew and FHS teacher Brenna Johnson have been invited to participate in a series of events in New York City at Carnegie Hall!

Please join us in congratulating Drew and the FPS Visual Art Department on this incredible achievement! A few examples of Drew's ceramic work are attached. Bravo!

Franklin Cultural Council
March 14 at 11:41 AM ·

The FCC is announcing a town-wide ONLINE ART CONTEST the week of March 16th geared towards elementary and middle school students! There will be two winners per day; one elementary school student and one middle school student. Prizes will be hand delivered to your mailbox!

Monday, Make Art with Nature
Tuesday, Create Art with Paint
Wednesday, Create Art with Recycles
Thursday, Create a Collage of your Pet
Friday, Create Sculpture Art

Photo examples will be available at the beginning of each day! Photo of your child's artwork should be submitted on the "post of the day" on the Franklin Cultural Council Facebook page with their name (or alias) and grade. One entry per student. Entries must be posted by 5pm each day.
Winners will be announced at 7pm each day!

Visit our Town Common and enjoy the display! Thank you to everyone who participated in this town-wide event! Kindness is catching! post_text:
This Wednesday, Franklin High School is hosting Franklin High Alum Kristi Kirshe. Kristi was a three-sport star at Franklin High (earned Gatorade Player of the Year in soccer) and went on to Williams College where she won the National Championship. Since college, she picked up the sort of rugby and in under a year's time, she earned a spot on Team USA's Women's Team and is currently preparing for the Olympics!
Please join us on Wednesday, February 12th at 7pm in the FHS auditorium. Kristi will be sharing about her life and the role sport has played in it. A great opportunity for students throughout our district!
